WorldStage Newsonline– Alhaji Lai Mohammed, Nigeria’s Minister of Information and Culture has expressed appreciation to all All Progressive Congress (APC) members and supporters in Kwara State for their unflinching commitment against the backdrop of the recent events at the National Assembly where some members crossed carpet to the opposition Peoples Democratic Party (PDP). Mohammed, a politician from Kwara State, same with the Senate President, Dr Bukola Saraki in a statement said, the commitment of supporters in Kwara State had been reflected in the overwhelming support and solidarity received, not just from our party members but also from other parties and stakeholders across the state, “since the melodrama at the National Assembly on Tuesday. “In particular, there has been an expression of overwhelming love and support for President Muhammadu Buhari from across Kwara, in the wake of the defections by federal legislators from Kwara.” He called on all our members and supporters in Kwara to remain calm, saying, “there is no cause for alarm. “We are currently consulting with the national leadership of our great party, with a view to coming up with a programme of action that will take into consideration the recent developments. “Our members and supporters should have no doubt whatsoever that whatever decisions we take after the consultations will be in their overall best interest.”